and go back to the old you.

578
00:42:55,910 --> 00:42:56,920
Okay?

579
00:43:13,250 --> 00:43:15,530
Are you sure you guys have no idea?

580
00:43:15,890 --> 00:43:17,430
I definitely put the handkerchief

581
00:43:17,510 --> 00:43:18,970
in the drawer right there.

582
00:43:19,050 --> 00:43:20,680
As soon as I got discharged,
I put it there

583
00:43:20,770 --> 00:43:23,720
and never took it out.
But that handkerchief is gone!

584
00:43:25,080 --> 00:43:26,970
-Young Lady.
-How does this make sense?

585
00:43:27,060 --> 00:43:29,220
They've neither seen nor touched it.

586
00:43:29,310 --> 00:43:30,540
Are you telling me

587
00:43:30,630 --> 00:43:32,080
that a handkerchief somehow

588
00:43:32,170 --> 00:43:33,750
walked out of the house and left?

589
00:43:34,280 --> 00:43:36,210
Her old self is back,
and so is her temper.

590
00:43:36,300 --> 00:43:37,970
Please!

591
00:43:44,180 --> 00:43:45,670
I'm begging you.

592
00:43:46,640 --> 00:43:49,020
When you clean my room and Kim Dan's room,

593
00:43:49,940 --> 00:43:52,100
please do not touch anything in the rooms.

594
00:43:55,620 --> 00:43:57,160
The person who finds the handkerchief

595
00:43:57,240 --> 00:43:59,090
will get 200 percent
of the paycheck as a bonus.

596
00:44:26,110 --> 00:44:27,650
Why did you call the doctor?

597
00:44:27,740 --> 00:44:29,100
I told you I was fine.

598
00:44:29,190 --> 00:44:30,550
If you were fine,

599
00:44:30,640 --> 00:44:31,700
why would you come to the park
on rainy days

600
00:44:31,780 --> 00:44:32,880
like a crazy woman?

601
00:44:33,150 --> 00:44:34,820
And if you were fine,
why would you talk to yourself

602
00:44:34,910 --> 00:44:36,580
when there's no one around you at home?

603
00:44:51,500 --> 00:44:53,390
How long does it take to brew this?

604
00:44:53,700 --> 00:44:54,660
No matter how much I try,

605
00:44:54,750 --> 00:44:56,600
it doesn't taste like your tea.

606
00:45:00,560 --> 00:45:02,800
About three minutes?
Won't the tea be too bitter then?

607
00:45:05,090 --> 00:45:06,410
It's too hot.

608
00:45:11,300 --> 00:45:13,940
Don't just stand there. Come and hold me.

609
00:45:14,330 --> 00:45:15,300
Come on.

610
00:45:18,420 --> 00:45:19,960
No, I mean...

611
00:45:20,710 --> 00:45:22,690
I did that
because I saw an illusion of him.

612
00:45:22,780 --> 00:45:24,850
And that hallucination is a symptom.

613
00:45:24,940 --> 00:45:26,960
Trauma. Stress.

614
00:45:29,690 --> 00:45:32,500
Actually, when we first met,

615
00:45:32,900 --> 00:45:34,570
I sensed that he was there.

616
00:45:34,750 --> 00:45:36,990
No one could see him,
but I was the only one who could.

617
00:45:37,430 --> 00:45:39,450
So the Kim Dan I'm seeing right now

618
00:45:40,290 --> 00:45:42,310
might be real. No?

619
00:45:43,850 --> 00:45:45,260
I'll prescribe you medicine.

620
00:45:45,390 --> 00:45:47,770
Make sure you take your medicine.

621
00:46:03,570 --> 00:46:04,580
Young Lady.

622
00:46:07,220 --> 00:46:08,190
Want to have some soju?

623
00:46:10,610 --> 00:46:12,100
You won't take the medicine, will you?

624
00:46:13,470 --> 00:46:14,480
You can drink it then.

625
00:46:15,670 --> 00:46:17,950
Sometimes, this is better than medicine.

626
00:46:19,490 --> 00:46:21,430
Ms. Jung, give me back the handkerchief.

627
00:46:22,930 --> 00:46:24,860
I'm telling the truth. I didn't take it.

628
00:46:24,950 --> 00:46:27,680
You are the only one who hates Kim Dan.

629
00:46:30,320 --> 00:46:31,330
Darn it.

630
00:46:40,310 --> 00:46:41,490
What's this?

631
00:46:41,580 --> 00:46:43,650
Mementos to people who were left behind.

632
00:46:43,910 --> 00:46:45,320
And trash to people

633
00:46:45,670 --> 00:46:46,730
who ran away.

634
00:46:55,180 --> 00:46:56,540
His clothes are still here.

635
00:47:00,720 --> 00:47:02,220
All of his stuff is still here.

636
00:47:02,610 --> 00:47:03,760
Where on earth did he...

637
00:47:17,970 --> 00:47:19,330
(Happy first wedding anniversary!)

638
00:47:21,140 --> 00:47:23,380
Why did you give me this now?

639
00:47:23,470 --> 00:47:26,460
Look how he wrote those
even before your performance.

640
00:47:26,550 --> 00:47:28,400
He was already thinking about
leaving then.

641
00:47:28,570 --> 00:47:30,990
That's why he was in a rush
to get married.

642
00:47:31,080 --> 00:47:32,310
This is Kim Dan's

643
00:47:34,780 --> 00:47:35,880
handwriting.

644
00:47:39,180 --> 00:47:40,190
(Happy first wedding anniversary!)

645
00:47:40,280 --> 00:47:41,730
Happy first wedding anniversary!

646
00:47:44,190 --> 00:47:46,830
(This is the first letter
I wrote to a human, not the deity.)

647
00:47:46,960 --> 00:47:48,060
Isn't it an honor?

648
00:47:51,540 --> 00:47:52,680
(Happy second wedding anniversary!
I love you.)

649
00:47:52,770 --> 00:47:55,280
(Happy second wedding anniversary!
I love you.)

650
00:48:02,320 --> 00:48:04,040
(Happy third wedding anniversary!)

651
00:48:04,260 --> 00:48:05,840
(Did the rape flowers bloom beautifully?)

652
00:48:09,180 --> 00:48:10,680
(Happy 10th wedding anniversary!)

653
00:48:11,650 --> 00:48:14,510
(Gosh, you're still not over me?)

654
00:48:18,470 --> 00:48:20,180
(Happy 30th wedding anniversary!)

655
00:48:20,840 --> 00:48:21,860
(I still)

656
00:48:22,910 --> 00:48:24,060
(love you the same.)

657
00:48:31,670 --> 00:48:32,680
Wait...

658
00:48:42,180 --> 00:48:45,090
I really shouldn't drink too much.

659
00:48:47,290 --> 00:48:48,390
Drink up.

660
00:48:49,360 --> 00:48:50,720
Drink up and forget everything.

661
00:48:51,820 --> 00:48:52,880
Forget it.

662
00:48:54,990 --> 00:48:56,130
Exactly.

663
00:48:57,890 --> 00:49:01,020
I heard brain cells get damaged
when someone drinks.

664
00:49:01,240 --> 00:49:04,230
That means I'll forget.
No, I can't do that.

665
00:49:04,980 --> 00:49:07,830
I won't even forget an eyelash on him.

666
00:49:10,610 --> 00:49:13,910
Young Lady, pull yourself together.

667
00:49:15,140 --> 00:49:19,490
I really feel like Kim Dan is with me.

668
00:49:20,680 --> 00:49:22,710
I keep seeing him.

669
00:49:24,550 --> 00:49:25,920
Look over there.

670
00:49:27,020 --> 00:49:29,130
He's standing right there.

671
00:49:29,480 --> 00:49:30,760
Kim Dan!

672
00:49:30,980 --> 00:49:34,230
What's over there? Nothing is there.

673
00:49:34,760 --> 00:49:37,230
You're scaring me. Stop it.

674
00:49:37,970 --> 00:49:39,950
Did I really go crazy?

675
00:49:40,790 --> 00:49:41,980
You can take medicine.

676
00:49:42,990 --> 00:49:45,280
You can talk to a doctor and get treated.

677
00:49:45,370 --> 00:49:48,090
No. If I take medicine,

678
00:49:49,020 --> 00:49:50,430
I won't be able to see him.

679
00:49:51,040 --> 00:49:52,320
If I get treated,

680
00:49:52,410 --> 00:49:54,910
I won't be able to see him anymore.

681
00:49:55,270 --> 00:49:58,130
If I can see him
because I have gone insane,

682
00:49:59,180 --> 00:50:02,350
then I wish to remain insane.

683
00:50:02,440 --> 00:50:04,070
I just want to be crazy 24 hours a day,

684
00:50:04,150 --> 00:50:05,740
365 days a year.

685
00:50:05,830 --> 00:50:06,930
But...

686
00:50:08,030 --> 00:50:10,620
But I can't live like that.

687
00:50:11,280 --> 00:50:15,770
He gave me his life.
He gave me this breath.

688
00:50:15,860 --> 00:50:19,200
I have to live really well

689
00:50:19,510 --> 00:50:24,220
because I have to live for Kim Dan too.

690
00:50:28,710 --> 00:50:30,250
I miss you.

691
00:50:31,480 --> 00:50:33,280
I want to hug you.

692
00:50:35,090 --> 00:50:37,770
I want to smell you, Kim Dan.

693
00:51:08,880 --> 00:51:11,960
(Report)

694
00:51:15,700 --> 00:51:17,900
(After wandering
around the deep darkness,)

695
00:51:18,730 --> 00:51:21,280
(Angel Kim Dan
reports back with another mission.)

696
00:51:30,830 --> 00:51:32,640
How long does it take to brew this?

697
00:51:32,900 --> 00:51:35,670
No matter how much I try,
it doesn't taste like your tea.

698
00:51:36,950 --> 00:51:38,880
About three minutes?

699
00:51:45,480 --> 00:51:48,080
Don't just stand there. Come and hold me.

700
00:51:50,280 --> 00:51:51,290
Come on.

701
00:51:58,770 --> 00:52:00,660
He's standing right there.

702
00:52:00,840 --> 00:52:01,980
Kim Dan!

703
00:52:02,510 --> 00:52:05,640
What's over there? Nothing is there.

704
00:52:06,650 --> 00:52:08,850
(-Thank you.)
-You're scaring me. Stop it.

705
00:52:08,980 --> 00:52:10,830
(You let me stay with her)

706
00:52:11,800 --> 00:52:13,730
(even if she cannot see me.)

707
00:52:14,790 --> 00:52:15,930
(It's all right.)

708
00:52:16,900 --> 00:52:18,400
(Even if she doesn't know to the end,)

709
00:52:18,480 --> 00:52:20,070
(even if nobody knows,)

710
00:52:21,170 --> 00:52:23,240
(even if I must just watch her forever,)

711
00:52:24,600 --> 00:52:26,050
(it's all right with me.)

712
00:52:43,120 --> 00:52:44,490
This is disappointing.

713
00:52:44,750 --> 00:52:46,690
I wanted to perform one more time
with you.

714
00:52:46,770 --> 00:52:49,190
You won't listen to me
and dance the way you want anyway.

715
00:52:49,550 --> 00:52:50,870
And there was fun in creating

716
00:52:50,950 --> 00:52:52,410
a piece of that, wasn't there?

717
00:52:55,220 --> 00:52:56,230
Thank you for everything.

718
00:52:58,570 --> 00:52:59,670
Me too.

719
00:53:00,770 --> 00:53:02,700
Are you sure you'll leave
without seeing the corps?

720
00:53:02,970 --> 00:53:04,950
I hate doing something like that.

721
00:53:05,080 --> 00:53:06,440
It's embarrassing and awkward.

722
00:53:06,620 --> 00:53:07,760
Okay, then.

723
00:53:12,030 --> 00:53:13,130
Director Ji.

724
00:53:15,900 --> 00:53:17,220
Do you feel

725
00:53:18,150 --> 00:53:19,510
more at ease now?

726
00:53:28,530 --> 00:53:30,470
Is there a principal dancer
you're looking for?

727
00:53:31,130 --> 00:53:32,530
Not sure. I'll look for one.

728
00:53:33,900 --> 00:53:35,920
There is a great ballerina I know.

729
00:53:36,360 --> 00:53:37,420
Do you want to meet her?

730
00:53:44,060 --> 00:53:45,690
You can't run away like this.

731
00:53:45,780 --> 00:53:48,150
You should try to lose your temper
when you're in New York.

732
00:53:49,910 --> 00:53:51,450
Thank you for everything.

733
00:53:51,540 --> 00:53:53,480
Keep up your good work
no matter where you go.

734
00:53:55,280 --> 00:53:58,930
Eun-young, Woo-jin.
Lower the lift for the judgment.

735
00:53:59,020 --> 00:54:00,910
Soo-ji, make sure
you always watch your shoulders.

736
00:54:01,000 --> 00:54:02,010
And...

737
00:54:02,190 --> 00:54:04,830
Come on, you're nagging us
until the very end.

738
00:54:05,140 --> 00:54:06,940
Just make sure you look after yourself.

739
00:54:09,490 --> 00:54:12,440
Thanks. Great work. Great work, everyone.

740
00:54:12,530 --> 00:54:13,450
Thank you. Great work.

741
00:54:13,540 --> 00:54:14,950
-Thank you, Director Ji.
-Thank you.

742
00:54:15,040 --> 00:54:16,750
-Let's take a picture.
-Time for a picture.

743
00:54:17,900 --> 00:54:18,910
Okay.

744
00:54:19,530 --> 00:54:21,510
Make sure your face is shown.

745
00:54:21,590 --> 00:54:23,260
-Lower it a little.
-I can't see myself.

746
00:54:23,350 --> 00:54:26,920
-Okay, Fantasia!
-Fantasia!

747
00:54:35,940 --> 00:54:36,950
One.

748
00:54:38,530 --> 00:54:40,950
Up. And down.

749
00:54:42,100 --> 00:54:44,120
You shouldn't look in the mirror.

750
00:54:44,210 --> 00:54:46,670
Down. To your fingertips.

751
00:54:48,120 --> 00:54:49,310
Your eyes.

752
00:54:49,490 --> 00:54:50,590
Come here.

753
00:54:50,810 --> 00:54:53,010
What did I say you need to look at
when you're dancing?

754
00:54:53,100 --> 00:54:54,720
-Myself.
-You're right.

755
00:54:54,810 --> 00:54:57,450
What do you think you became
when you hear this music?

756
00:54:57,540 --> 00:54:59,210
Like a cloud in the sky.

757
00:54:59,300 --> 00:55:01,980
Right? Then you can feel that
when you try again.

758
00:55:02,070 --> 00:55:04,100
Everyone, let's take it from the top.

759
00:55:19,540 --> 00:55:22,180
That's a cup of drip coffee. Very fancy.

760
00:55:23,100 --> 00:55:25,610
I have to save in order to pay my rent.

761
00:55:28,430 --> 00:55:31,600
I heard you're going to New York.
Yi-geon told me.

762
00:55:31,680 --> 00:55:32,870
Congratulations.

763
00:55:33,930 --> 00:55:36,700
Are you sure you don't want to
return as a performer?

764
00:55:37,670 --> 00:55:39,380
I think this fits me the best.

765
00:55:39,470 --> 00:55:42,110
Dancing happily with children.

766
00:55:42,640 --> 00:55:43,700
I feel content.

767
00:55:44,840 --> 00:55:46,690
If you change your mind,
come whenever you want.

768
00:55:46,860 --> 00:55:50,740
I'm an expert
on bringing back a ballerina who retired.

769
00:55:53,070 --> 00:55:56,500
When we meet again, I hope I can meet you

770
00:55:56,850 --> 00:55:58,960
as a human, not a ballerina.

771
00:56:24,040 --> 00:56:27,340
I'm glad that she has been
taking the medicine.

772
00:56:29,450 --> 00:56:31,170
It's not even raining.

773
00:56:31,790 --> 00:56:33,680
Where did Young Lady go?

774
00:56:39,130 --> 00:56:41,110
Everything is going back to its place.

775
00:56:42,610 --> 00:56:44,770
I guess they are all going back
to the beginning.

776
00:56:52,990 --> 00:56:56,030
But you aren't here.

777
00:56:59,290 --> 00:57:01,220
I can't see you as a hallucination either.

778
00:57:04,700 --> 00:57:06,280
I'll be brave.

779
00:57:06,850 --> 00:57:09,490
I'll believe that you are watching me
from somewhere.

780
00:57:58,950 --> 00:58:00,180
Nothing is written on it again.

781
00:58:01,060 --> 00:58:02,860
This is a huge scam.

782
00:58:02,950 --> 00:58:04,930
I never even found one!

783
00:58:15,400 --> 00:58:16,420
(Today.)

784
00:58:17,080 --> 00:58:18,090
(Right here.)

785
00:58:24,030 --> 00:58:25,350
This is so weird.

786
00:58:30,760 --> 00:58:32,830
I only spent

787
00:58:33,970 --> 00:58:35,690
a season with Kim Dan.

788
00:58:40,310 --> 00:58:41,850
But why do I

789
00:58:43,870 --> 00:58:46,030
feel completely empty?

790
00:58:51,260 --> 00:58:53,380
I will be brave.

791
00:58:53,510 --> 00:58:54,830
I will.

792
00:58:56,500 --> 00:58:57,640
But...

793
00:58:59,180 --> 00:59:02,180
But let me think of you
and cry from time to time.

794
00:59:31,570 --> 00:59:33,720
Yeon-seo, pull yourself together.

795
00:59:45,820 --> 00:59:46,880
Kim Dan.

796
00:59:48,510 --> 00:59:50,220
Kim Dan, come out.

797
01:00:51,340 --> 01:00:52,440
Can you

798
01:00:53,140 --> 01:00:54,240
see me?

799
01:00:59,170 --> 01:01:01,060
How can this happen?

800
01:01:03,040 --> 01:01:04,100
I knew

801
01:01:07,090 --> 01:01:08,190
you would come.

802
01:01:18,840 --> 01:01:21,480
(This is my final report.)

803
01:01:22,890 --> 01:01:26,230
(It is very interesting
to observe humans.)

804
01:01:27,330 --> 01:01:29,790
(If the time of eternity
is colored in black and white,)

805
01:01:30,670 --> 01:01:32,170
(humans shine in all kinds of colors,)

806
01:01:32,260 --> 01:01:33,930
(as if they can be shattered
at any moment.)

807
01:01:34,940 --> 01:01:36,480
(That's why it makes them interesting.)

808
01:01:37,400 --> 01:01:38,770
(When the mission is over,)

809
01:01:39,120 --> 01:01:41,190
(everything will return to its place.)

810
01:01:42,290 --> 01:01:44,000
(Humans will die and disappear.)

811
01:01:44,660 --> 01:01:47,830
(Angels will fly around forever.)

812
01:01:49,060 --> 01:01:50,300
(That is the deity's...)

813
01:01:50,960 --> 01:01:52,360
(The universe's providence.)

814
01:01:54,210 --> 01:01:57,200
(We will live happily
with this miraculous love)

815
01:01:57,910 --> 01:01:59,540
(within that providence,)

816
01:02:00,990 --> 01:02:02,700
(brilliantly and dangerously,)

817
01:02:03,540 --> 01:02:05,210
(as we shine radiantly.)

818
01:02:12,600 --> 01:02:16,210
(Angel's Last Mission: Love)
